@startuml Slot 6: ARC-to-Agrischemas Domain-Specific Mapping
!theme plain

title Slot 6: ARC-based Middleware — Domain-Specific Object Exchange

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<arc>> #FEF3C7
  BackgroundColor<<agrischemas>> #DBEAFE
  BackgroundColor<<gap>> #FEE2E2
  BorderColor #666
}

package "ARC RO-Crate Entities (Domain-Specific)" <<arc>> {
  [Investigation\nisa:Investigation] as INV
  [Study\nisa:Study] as STUDY
  [Assay\nisa:Assay] as ASSAY
  [Factor] as FACTOR
  [Protocol] as PROTOCOL
  [Source / Sample / Material] as MAT
}

package "Agrischemas Profiles (Aspirational)" <<agrischemas>> {
  [FieldTrialStudy\nagrischemas:FieldTrialStudy] as FT
  [CropVariety\nagrischemas:CropVariety] as CV
}

package "Mapping Coverage" <<gap>> {
  [title -> title\nexact match] as M1
  [description -> description\nexact match] as M2
  [startDate -> startDate\nexact match] as M3
  [contacts.name -> contact\ntransform] as M4
  [study.design -> experimentalDesign\nsemantic] as M5
  [??? -> location\nMISSING - must be supplied] as GAP1
  [??? -> crop\nsemantic gap - derive from study] as GAP2
  [??? -> variety\nMISSING in CropVariety] as GAP3
  [??? -> registrationYear\nMISSING in CropVariety] as GAP4
}

' ARC -> Agrischemas mapping
INV --> FT : Investigation\nmaps to Study context
STUDY --> FT : Study fields\nmap to trial metadata
ASSAY --> FT : Assay provides\nexperimental data
FACTOR --> FT : Factors define\nexperimental conditions

INV --> CV : Investigation context
STUDY --> CV : Study provides\nvariety context

' Coverage flows
M1 ..> FT : title
M2 ..> FT : description
M3 ..> FT : startDate
M4 ..> FT : contact
M5 ..> FT : experimentalDesign
GAP1 ..> FT : location needed
GAP2 ..> FT : crop inference needed
GAP3 ..> CV : variety needed
GAP4 ..> CV : registrationYear needed

note bottom of FT
  Agrischemas is aspirational:
  in development, not yet adopted
  by RDIs. RDI metadata currently
  comes as Schema.org, INSPIRE,
  CSV, SQL — not Agrischemas.
  These profiles define the
  modeling target for ARCs.
end note

@enduml
